Biomedical Laboratory

                   Monitoring of Electroencephalogram (EEG) signal for different lobes.



Bipolar Recording -
Leads Fz,Cz and Pz from different lobes are connected for bipolar mode of recording of EEG signals.





STEP 1 : Make all the Correct Connections.

1.  Connect Fz lead point of human brain to the positive terminal (Fz) of first op-amp circuit.

2.  Connect Cz lead point of human brain to the terminal (Cz) of op-amp circuit.

3.  Connect Pz lead point of human brain to the negative terminal (Pz) of op-amp circuit.

                      

STEP 2 : Click on check button to check for Correct Connections.

STEP 3 : If Connections are not correct click on reset button for reset connections.

STEP 4 : If Connections are correct click on play/pause button to see recorded EEG signals for Fz-Cz-Pz.

STEP 5 : Click on waveform tab for data obsevation and measurement.

STEP 6 : Click on print button to save the observations.
